title: CNBC tech editor on the Apple-Facebook clash over personal data
text: Facebook last week blasted Apple's decision to prompt iPhone users to disable apps from tracking their personal data. CNBC technology editor Steve Kovach and Danny Fortson, The Sunday Times West Coast correspondent, joins 'Closing Bell' to talk about the fight between Apple and Facebook over personal data.

title: Goldman Sees Double-Digit Gains for Alphabet and Facebook Stock. Here's Why.
text: Multi-front legal battles shouldn't crimp growth for Alphabet and Facebook stock in the next year, according to Goldman Sachs.

title: The latest skirmish between Facebook and Apple is part of a fight that stretches back more than a decade
text: Facebook launched a campaign last week blasting Apple's decision to prompt iPhone users to disable apps from tracking their personal data.

title: Report: Authorities Rejected Facebook Offer to Foster Competitors' Growth
text: Antitrust regulators didn't believe the offer went far enough to break the social network's monopolistic grasp.

title: 5 Stocks to Ride the Virtual Reality Wave in 2021 & Beyond
text: Here we discuss five stocks, FB, SNE, AAPL, MSFT and U, which are expected to benefit from the rapidly growing virtual reality market.

title: FAAMG is Highly Overvalued: Is it Worth Paying the Premium?
text: The FAAMG stocks -- FB, AMZN, AAPL, MSFT & GOOGL -- despite being pricey are expected to maintain momentum in 2021 based on rapid adoption of cloud computing and 5G.

title: FANG Stocks: A Hopeless Quest For Outsized Returns
text: The elite group of FANG stocks undoubtedly falls into the "EVA Monsters" category, where the majority of our expected return stems from future growth in EVA. In the case of "EVA Monsters", the primary pitfalls are that we either overpay for growth or that the forecasted growth does not materialize to the extent we expected.
